 lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Matthias","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament Greek form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i> (  see  Matthew  ), or rather of an Aramaic derivative. The Latin form of the name is <i>Matthaeus</i>. In English the form <i>Matthias</i> is used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament to distinguish the disciple who was chosen after the treachery of Judas to make up the twelve (Acts 1:23–26) from the evangelist <i>Matthew</i>. However, this distinction is not observed in other languages, where <i>Matthias</i> (or a version of it) is often a learned doublet existing alongside a vernacular derivative."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathias","meanings":["and Norwegian: learned doublet of   Mads ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Matthias von Volkenshagen was born in 1280, in Ribnitz, Mecklenburg-Schwerin, Germany, his father, Thye de Ribbenitze, was 31 and his mother, Mrs Thye de Ribbenitze, was 33. He had at least 1 daughter with Gese Kröpelin. He died in 1327, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1280–1327":"1280–1327","1285–1310":"1285–1310","1310–1330":"1310–1330","1250–1318":"1250–1318","1248–Female":"1248–Surnud","1327":"1327","1248":"1248","1310":"1310","efter 1318":"pärast 1318","1330":"1330","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","omkring 1310":"umbes 1310","1280":"1280","1318":"1318","efter 1310":"pärast 1310","Rostock, Rostock, Mecklenburg-Schwerin, Tyskland":"Rostock, Stadt Rostock, Großherzogtum Mecklenburg-Schwerin","Ribnitz, Mecklenburg-Schwerin, Tyskland":"Ribnitz, Freistaat Mecklenburg-Schwerin, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1280–1327":"1280–1327","1285–1310":"1285–1310","1310–1330":"1310–1330","1250–1318":"1250–1318","1248–Female":"1248–Kuollut","1327":"1327","1248":"1248","1310"